Lé Vibe — quick steps after apt install
=======================================

1. Install a Code - OSS–compatible editor (e.g. VSCodium at /usr/bin/codium). Package recommends: codium.

**`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`:** If your editor binary is not the default, set **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** to a full path or a command on **`PATH`** before **`lvibe`**. When you build the Lé Vibe IDE from **`editor/`** in the monorepo, point **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** at that binary (see **`editor/README.md`** in the source tree). This **`le-vibe`** package does not install the IDE binary by itself.

**Session persistence (14.g):** Interactive shells can **`export LE_VIBE_EDITOR=...`** in **`~/.profile`** or **`~/.bashrc`**. **Desktop / “open from app menu”** sessions often **do not** source those files — use **`~/.config/environment.d/`** (`*.conf`, systemd user environment) or your distro’s documented session env so **`lvibe`** inherits **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** (same story as **`editor/README.md`** *Persisting `LE_VIBE_EDITOR`*).

**Default editor when `LE_VIBE_EDITOR` is unset (14.g):** the launcher uses the same order as **`le_vibe.launcher._default_editor`** in **`le-vibe/le_vibe/launcher.py`**: **`$LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** if set; else **`/usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium`** if that path exists and is executable (**`le-vibe-ide`** **`.deb`** — **`packaging/debian-le-vibe-ide/`**; **PRODUCT_SPEC** §7.3 internal install path, not a second public **`PATH`** CLI); else **`/usr/bin/codium`** if executable; else the command **`codium`** on **`PATH`**. **`debian/control`** **`Recommends: codium`** and **`Suggests: le-vibe-ide`** cover the usual cases: stock VSCodium until the optional IDE package is installed from the same release train.

**`le-vibe-ide` package (14.g / §7.3):** A separate Debian source under **`packaging/debian-le-vibe-ide/`** installs the built **`VSCode-linux-*/`** tree under **`/usr/lib/le-vibe/ide/`** and exposes **`/usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium`** for the stack launcher. Build flow: compile in **`editor/vscodium/`** (**`editor/BUILD.md`**), run **`packaging/scripts/stage-le-vibe-ide-deb.sh`**, then **`dpkg-buildpackage`** from **`packaging/debian-le-vibe-ide/`** (see that directory’s **`README.md`**). **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** still overrides for custom layouts (**`~/.config/environment.d/`**, **`/etc/profile.d/`**—same as **`editor/BUILD.md`** *14.g*).

2. Run the launcher once so first-run can install Ollama (if needed), pull a model, and write configs under ~/.config/le-vibe/:
     lvibe
   (Compatibility: `le-vibe` is the same entrypoint.)

3. Wire Continue in one step (as your normal user, not root):
     le-vibe-setup-continue
   Exit codes are documented in the main README (0 ok; 1 need first-run; 2 sync; 3 extension; 4 no editor).

4. Open the editor, confirm Continue uses apiBase http://127.0.0.1:11435 (managed Ollama).

IDE sources in a clone (developers)
------------------------------------
End users who only install this **`.deb`** do not need the monorepo. If you **do** have a full clone with **`editor/vscodium`** initialized — typically **`git submodule update --init --recursive`**, or **`git submodule update --init editor/vscodium`** for the VSCodium tree alone (**Fresh clone (14.b)** — **`editor/README.md`**) — run **`./editor/smoke.sh`** from the repository root to exercise the same **H6** layout and script checks as **`build-le-vibe-ide.yml`** / **`build-linux.yml`** (no Electron compile — the latter is a manual **`workflow_dispatch`** alias). On **GitHub Actions**, **`build-le-vibe-ide`** uploads pre-binary **`ide-ci-metadata.txt`** (**`le_vibe_editor_docs`**) with **`upload-artifact`** **`retention-days`**, declares workflow **`permissions:`** **`contents: read`**, **`actions: write`** (checkout + artifact upload), and the job **Summary** includes **Pre-binary artifact** / **`LE_VIBE_EDITOR`** (see **`editor/BUILD.md`** *CI*, **`editor/VENDORING.md`**). Optional job **`linux_compile`** (not the default **`pull_request`** path) runs **`ci-vscodium-linux-dev-build.sh`** → **`dev/build.sh`**; that wrapper enforces **`node --version`** vs **`editor/.nvmrc`** before **`dev/build.sh`** (**14.e** / **14.a**; **`LEVIBE_SKIP_NODE_VERSION_CHECK`** — **`editor/BUILD.md`** *Compile wrapper vs Node*). See **`editor/README.md`** and **`docs/ci-qa-hardening.md`** (*IDE smoke*).

**Honesty (14.d):** that fast **`./editor/smoke.sh`** / **`ci-editor-gate`** gate checks vendoring + scripts only — not Lé Vibe–visible IDE branding. Staging map **`editor/le-vibe-overrides/branding-staging.checklist.md`** — read *PRODUCT_SPEC §7.2 (read before overrides)* first (**`docs/PRODUCT_SPEC.md` §7.2**); **`editor/README.md`** *14.c vs 14.d*; repository **`README.md`** *CI*.

Model lock (inspectable)
------------------------
Hardware tiering picks a **concrete** Ollama model tag for this machine. It is stored as:
  ~/.config/le-vibe/locked-model.json
together with `model-decision.json` and `continue-config.yaml`. The product does **not** persist a vague AUTODETECT-only lock when a real tag is known.

Workspace `.lvibe/`
-------------------
When you open a folder (e.g. `lvibe .`), the launcher asks for **workspace memory** consent on first use (**`PRODUCT_SPEC` §5**). If you **accept**, it prepares **`.lvibe/`** at the project root, appends **`.lvibe/`** to `.gitignore` when a `.gitignore` already exists, and adds small agent-oriented files for token-efficient local memory. If you **decline**, no **`.lvibe/`** folder is created.

Authority (clone the upstream repository)
------------------------------------------
Must-ship product requirements: **`docs/PRODUCT_SPEC.md`**. Maintainer index (Roadmap **H1–H8**): **`docs/README.md`**. Formal roster of orchestration docs: **`PRODUCT_SPEC` §9** (*Relationship to existing specs*). **E1 / acceptance:** **`docs/PRODUCT_SPEC_SECTION8_EVIDENCE.md`** — maps **`le-vibe/tests/`** to §5–§10 (clone the upstream tree to run **`pytest`**). Full **E1** roster — project root **`README.md`** (*Tests* / **E1 mapping**); **`docs/spec-phase2.md` §14** *Honesty vs CI*. **Privacy / reporting:** **`docs/privacy-and-telemetry.md`** (*E1 contract tests* row); **`SECURITY.md`** (**`Related docs`** lists **`docs/README`** *Product surface* — **H8** **`.github/`** — **`ci.yml`**, **`dependabot.yml`**, **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`** + **`config.yml`** **`#` H8** + **`privacy-and-telemetry`** *E1*; and optional **`docs/rag/le-vibe-phase2-chunks.md`** — *RAG / embeddings*, **`spec-phase2.md` §14*, non-canonical).

**Phase 2 scope (this `.deb` vs fork / Flatpak):** In an upstream clone, read **`docs/spec-phase2.md` §14** — this source package ships launcher + bootstrap + configs; a **branded editor-only** binary (**H6**) and **in-repo** Flatpak/AppImage (**H7**) are **not** claimed from this repository alone.

See /usr/share/doc/le-vibe/README and LICENSE. Upstream README: project repository.
